# Ticket Writing Conventions

Based on the AAIE Bear Eng<>Ops Team Guide to Ticket Creation.

## Title Format
`[Tool Type] [Project Name] - Ask summary`

Examples:
- "AT Tooling - [Project Odysseus] Modify Autoreviewer to check spelling"
- "RLS - [Project Mercury] Fix broken writer assignment flow"

## Required Fields

Every ticket description MUST include:

```
## Summary
1-2 sentences. What is needed and why it matters.

## Tool Links
Direct links to the relevant tool (Airtable/Hex/RLS), if applicable.

## Context
Clear explanation of the situation or problem. Include all relevant
details from the Slack thread so no context is missed.

## What is Being Blocked?
The specific step or process that is currently stopped or hindered.
This drives prioritization.

## Solution Spec
The ideal end state. Can be simple for small fixes, or reference a
doc with screenshots for larger asks. If ambiguous, note that scoping
help is needed.

## Timeline
The estimated date/time when the blocked step needs to proceed and why.

## Engineer with Context
If there is a specific engineer who has context, mention them.
If the reporter does not specify, ASK who should be assigned before
creating the ticket.
```

## Priority Guide

| Priority | Level | Criteria |
|----------|-------|----------|
| Urgent (P0) | 1 | Experience-breaking, can't do tasks; customer asked ASAP; more important than almost all other tickets |
| High (P1) | 2 | Blocking project start; blocking key improvement; tight 24hr SLA needed |
| Medium (P2) | 3 | Important but nice-to-have; ~3 days delivery acceptable |
| Low (P3) | 4 | Wishlist items |

Default SLA is 24 hours. If <24hr SLA is needed, the ticket must
explain why, and the reporter must DM Arunavha Chanda, Dylan Pourkay,
or the current oncall AND Jordan Winawer.

## After Creating a Ticket
Reply in the Slack thread with:
```
Created [IDENTIFIER]: [Title]
Priority: [level] · Assignee: [assignee or "Unassigned - pending triage"]
[linear URL]
```
